# Command istioctl

## What does this command do:

Istio configuration command line utility for service operators to debug and diagnose Istio mesh

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: curl -sSfL https://github.com/istio/istio/releases/download/1.29.2/istioctl-1.29.2-linux-amd64.tar.gz | tar -xz -C ~/.local/bin/ istioctl
For Raspberry Pi install using: curl -sSfL https://github.com/istio/istio/releases/download/1.29.2/istioctl-1.29.2-linux-arm64.tar.gz | tar -xz -C ~/.local/bin/ istioctl
For Mac install using: brew install istioctl

## Command path

For Fedora run: ~/.local/bin/istioctl
For Raspberry Pi run: ~/.local/bin/istioctl
For Mac run: /opt/homebrew/bin/istioctl

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://istio.io/latest/docs/reference/commands/istioctl/

## Command options

# Check client version (no cluster needed)
istioctl version --remote=false

# Print full version info including control plane
istioctl version

# Install Istio onto a cluster (uses default profile)
istioctl install --set profile=default

# Install with a specific profile (minimal, demo, default, ambient)
istioctl install --set profile=demo

# Uninstall Istio from a cluster
istioctl uninstall --purge

# Upgrade Istio in-place
istioctl upgrade

# Analyze cluster config for issues
istioctl analyze

# Analyze a specific namespace
istioctl analyze -n <namespace>

# Analyze local manifest files
istioctl analyze <file.yaml>

# Show proxy sync status for all sidecars
istioctl proxy-status

# Show proxy sync status for a specific pod
istioctl proxy-status <pod> -n <namespace>

# View proxy configuration (listeners, routes, clusters, endpoints)
istioctl proxy-config listener <pod> -n <namespace>
istioctl proxy-config route <pod> -n <namespace>
istioctl proxy-config cluster <pod> -n <namespace>
istioctl proxy-config endpoint <pod> -n <namespace>
istioctl proxy-config bootstrap <pod> -n <namespace>

# Inject Istio sidecar into a Kubernetes manifest
istioctl kube-inject -f deployment.yaml | kubectl apply -f -

# Manage revision tags
istioctl tag list
istioctl tag set <tag> --revision <rev>
istioctl tag generate <tag> --revision <rev>

# Manage waypoint proxies (ambient mode)
istioctl waypoint list
istioctl waypoint apply -n <namespace>
istioctl waypoint delete -n <namespace>

# Capture cluster diagnostics into a bug report archive
istioctl bug-report

# Open Istio web UIs (Kiali, Grafana, Jaeger, etc.)
istioctl dashboard kiali
istioctl dashboard grafana
istioctl dashboard jaeger
istioctl dashboard prometheus

# Control plane admin log levels
istioctl admin log --level debug

# Generate shell autocompletion
istioctl completion bash | sudo tee /etc/bash_completion.d/istioctl
istioctl completion zsh > ~/.zsh/completions/_istioctl

# Global flags
# -n, --namespace         Kubernetes namespace
# -i, --istioNamespace    Istio system namespace (default: istio-system)
# -c, --kubeconfig        Path to kubeconfig file
#     --context           Kubernetes config context
#     --vklog             Log verbosity level (e.g. --vklog=9)
